WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.920
Risk stratification is essential.

00:00:01.920 --> 00:00:05.280
Poor prognostic markers include biventricular dysfunction, late

00:00:05.280 --> 00:00:08.640
gadolinium enhancement on cardiac MRI — indicating

00:00:08.640 --> 00:00:12.000
irreversible fibrosis — Stage D heart failure

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:15.360
presentation, and giant cell histology on endomyocardial

00:00:15.360 --> 00:00:15.840
biopsy.

00:00:15.840 --> 00:00:19.200
Lymphocytic myocarditis carries the best prognosis, with

00:00:19.200 --> 00:00:22.560
approximately 50 percent of patients achieving full

00:00:22.560 --> 00:00:25.440
recovery within 2 to 4 weeks.

00:00:25.440 --> 00:00:28.800
Giant cell myocarditis, without transplant, has median

00:00:28.800 --> 00:00:31.200
survival of under 6 months.
